# How to Login and Use RiskBase

**The RiskBase App works on iOS, Android and your Web browser.**

Search for RiskBase in the [Apple App Store](https://apps.apple.com/gb/app/riskbase/id1533825779) or [Google Play Store](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=riskbase.client) or sign in on your device’s web browser at [app.riskbase.uk](https://app.riskbase.uk).

[filename](../_components/app_store.md ':include')

## Step 1: Sign in to the app using your email address

![][image1]

1. Open the RiskBase app.  
2. Enter your email address.  
3. Tap **Next**.  
4. We will email you a six-digit code. Enter the six digit code into the app to log in.

![][image2]

### Having trouble signing in?

RiskBase sends a unique login code every time you enter your email address, so you don't need a password. If you enter your email address and receive a code, but then go back and enter your email again and receive a new code, the first code won't work. 

To make sure you’re using the most recent login code:

1. Delete all the codes RiskBase has sent you.  
2. Enter your email address into RiskBase and wait for a new code to be emailed to you.  
3. Enter that code into RiskBase.

## Step 2: Start Using the Riskbase App

When you sign in to the RiskBase app for the first time or after logging out, you will see this page:  
![][image3]  
To get started from this landing page:

* Press **Download assets** (these are your properties, buildings, locations, etc).

### Assets Page

If you are currently signed in and have downloaded assets, you see the assets page populated with them.  
![][image4]  
To see how to perform assessments and other tasks for your Assets, check the How to section of the RiskBase documentation. 

## Step 3: Use RiskBase without an internet connection

Once you have downloaded the assets, you can work offline.  The data you input is being saved to your device and can be synced to RiskBase Cloud once you are back online.

![][image5]

To work offline with downloaded assets:

1. Select one or more assets by pressing on them.  
2. Press **Download**.  
3. Press **Done**.

![][image6]

### Don’t Lose Your Data, Make Sure You Remember To Sync\!

### **Don’t lose the data you enter while offline\!** Make sure that after you’ve made any changes to your Riskbase assets that you synchronise them back to the cloud, or you risk losing them if your device is broken, lost, or stolen. 

### An internet connection is required to download and sync assets

A mobile or Wi-Fi connection is required to download and sync Riskbase assets. data that is not synced will be lost if your device is lost or stolen.

Riskbase provides you with the tools to allow you to work offline and sync only the data your require, for example:

* A Fire Risk Assessor who performs an assessment once per year might only download an asset when an assessment is due, removing the asset when it is complete.   
* A housing manager who makes regular visits to buildings will likely keep all their assets downloaded on their device and regularly sync to the cloud.

**Your data is your responsibility, if you choose not to sync all of your data to the cloud, it is at your own risk.**
